  runs under) to check if it's actually installed in this venv.
- If missing, install it: `pip install Pillow` and add/confirm it's
  listed in requirements.txt (it should have been added in step 68 —
  check whether requirements.txt actually has it; if not, that's the
  root cause and needs fixing there so this doesn't happen again on a
  fresh venv).
- If it IS installed but the script still couldn't import it, figure
  out why (wrong venv/interpreter, import error, etc.) before
  proceeding — don't just reinstall blindly without understanding
  which case this is.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
STEP 2 — Make the test fail loudly instead of silently skipping
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

In scripts/test_openrouter_image_provider.py, find the dimension-decode
step (currently prints "Pillow not available — skipping dimension
decode" and continues to PASSED regardless). Change this so that if
Pillow is not importable, the script prints a clear error and exits
with a non-zero status instead of reporting PASSED — dimension
verification is the core purpose of this specific test, so its
absence must not be silently tolerated. Passing without checking the
one thing you set out to check is worse than not running the test at
all, since it creates false confidence.

